<p data-start="64" data-end="227">Since you're building <strong data-start="86" data-end="111">Digizura (CableMaker)</strong> and still developing pages, reducing the dropdown to 5 clear sections is actually the <strong data-start="198" data-end="226">correct product strategy</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="229" data-end="232">
<h2 data-start="234" data-end="272">✅ Why This Is Good for Your Website</h2>
<h3 data-start="274" data-end="304">1️⃣ Better User Experience</h3>
<p data-start="305" data-end="325">Too many menu items:</p>
<ul data-start="326" data-end="386">
<li data-start="326" data-end="347">
<p data-start="328" data-end="347">Confuses visitors</p>
</li>
<li data-start="348" data-end="365">
<p data-start="350" data-end="365">Feels complex</p>
</li>
<li data-start="366" data-end="386">
<p data-start="368" data-end="386">Looks unfinished</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="388" data-end="406">Simple navigation:</p>
<ul data-start="407" data-end="485">
<li data-start="407" data-end="424">
<p data-start="409" data-end="424">Feels premium</p>
</li>
<li data-start="425" data-end="447">
<p data-start="427" data-end="447">Easy to understand</p>
</li>
<li data-start="448" data-end="485">
<p data-start="450" data-end="485">Looks like a focused SaaS product</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="487" data-end="540">Modern SaaS websites usually keep navigation minimal.</p>
<hr data-start="542" data-end="545">
<h3 data-start="547" data-end="593">2️⃣ Faster Development (Important for You)</h3>
<p data-start="594" data-end="602">You are:</p>
<ul data-start="603" data-end="679">
<li data-start="603" data-end="618">
<p data-start="605" data-end="618">Building UI</p>
</li>
<li data-start="619" data-end="639">
<p data-start="621" data-end="639">Managing routing</p>
</li>
<li data-start="640" data-end="659">
<p data-start="642" data-end="659">Writing content</p>
</li>
<li data-start="660" data-end="679">
<p data-start="662" data-end="679">Handling layout</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="681" data-end="709">If you keep 15–20 pages now:</p>
<ul data-start="710" data-end="793">
<li data-start="710" data-end="738">
<p data-start="712" data-end="738">Development time increases</p>
</li>
<li data-start="739" data-end="762">
<p data-start="741" data-end="762">Maintenance increases</p>
</li>
<li data-start="763" data-end="793">
<p data-start="765" data-end="793">Inconsistency risk increases</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="795" data-end="813">With 5 main pages:</p>
<ul data-start="814" data-end="880">
<li data-start="814" data-end="839">
<p data-start="816" data-end="839">Cleaner Angular routing</p>
</li>
<li data-start="840" data-end="864">
<p data-start="842" data-end="864">Easier component reuse</p>
</li>
<li data-start="865" data-end="880">
<p data-start="867" data-end="880">Faster launch</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="882" data-end="885">
<h3 data-start="887" data-end="918">3️⃣ Looks More Professional</h3>
<p data-start="919" data-end="1006">Big companies group features under sections instead of making 1 page per small feature.</p>
<p data-start="1008" data-end="1068">For example structure style used in many ERP/SaaS platforms:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1070" data-end="1148"><div class="relative w-full my-4"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-eri7ssmm.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Code</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none size-9 rounded-full px-2 py-2 hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-eri7ssmm.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer"