<p data-start="1150" data-end="1176">That’s clean and scalable.</p>
<hr data-start="1178" data-end="1181">
<h3 data-start="1183" data-end="1211">4️⃣ SEO Is Not A Problem</h3>
<p data-start="1212" data-end="1220">You can:</p>
<ul data-start="1221" data-end="1329">
<li data-start="1221" data-end="1263">
<p data-start="1223" data-end="1263">Add all keywords inside those main pages</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1264" data-end="1294">
<p data-start="1266" data-end="1294">Use proper headings (H2, H3)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1295" data-end="1329">
<p data-start="1297" data-end="1329">Add feature sections inside page</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1331" data-end="1396">Later, if needed, you can split pages without breaking structure.</p>
<hr data-start="1398" data-end="1401">
<h2 data-start="1403" data-end="1435">⚠ When Should You NOT Reduce?</h2>
<p data-start="1437" data-end="1440">If:</p>
<ul data-start="1441" data-end="1566">
<li data-start="1441" data-end="1490">
<p data-start="1443" data-end="1490">You already have detailed feature documentation</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1491" data-end="1534">
<p data-start="1493" data-end="1534">Each feature needs separate SEO targeting</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1535" data-end="1566">
<p data-start="1537" data-end="1566">You have a large content team</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1568" data-end="1601">Right now, that’s not your stage.</p>
<hr data-start="1603" data-end="1606">
<h2 data-start="1608" data-end="1651">🎯 My Honest Recommendation for Digizura</h2>
<p data-start="1653" data-end="1711">Start simple.<br>
Launch clean.<br>
Validate product.<br>
Then expand.</p>
<p data-start="1713" data-end="1751">This is how strong SaaS products grow.</p>
