Now you’re thinking like a product owner, not just a developer.</p>
<p data-start="89" data-end="102">Short answer:</p>
<p data-start="104" data-end="204">👉 <strong data-start="107" data-end="144">Yes, they are important features.</strong><br data-start="144" data-end="147">
👉 <strong data-start="150" data-end="204">No, they are NOT all required in the top dropdown.</strong></p>
<p data-start="206" data-end="232">That’s the key difference.</p>
<hr data-start="234" data-end="237">
<h1 data-start="239" data-end="282">🎯 Let’s Think Like a Cable Factory Owner</h1>
<p data-start="284" data-end="359">If I am a Managing Director of a cable company, what do I care about first?</p>
<p data-start="361" data-end="374">I care about:</p>
<ol data-start="376" data-end="530">
<li data-start="376" data-end="408">
<p data-start="379" data-end="408">Production running smoothly</p>
</li>
<li data-start="409" data-end="437">
<p data-start="412" data-end="437">Stock not getting stuck</p>
</li>
<li data-start="438" data-end="467">
<p data-start="441" data-end="467">Orders getting delivered</p>
</li>
<li data-start="468" data-end="502">
<p data-start="471" data-end="502">Money &amp; costing under control</p>
</li>
<li data-start="503" data-end="530">
<p data-start="506" data-end="530">Multi-plant visibility</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="532" data-end="542">That’s it.</p>
<p data-start="544" data-end="621">I don’t open a website to see 15 small features.<br data-start="592" data-end="595">
I want high-level clarity.</p>
<hr data-start="623" data-end="626">
<h1 data-start="628" data-end="681">🔥 So What Is Truly “Most Important” For Mega Menu?</h1>
<p data-start="683" data-end="749">For CableMaker dropdown, the most powerful and clean structure is:</p>
<h3 data-start="751" data-end="765">OPERATIONS</h3>
<ul data-start="766" data-end="811">
<li data-start="766" data-end="789">
<p data-start="768" data-end="789">Production Planning</p>
</li>
<li data-start="790" data-end="811">
<p data-start="792" data-end="811">Quality Assurance</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="813" data-end="841">SUPPLY CHAIN (Inventory)</h3>
<ul data-start="842" data-end="866">
<li data-start="842" data-end="866">
<p data-start="844" data-end="866">Warehouse Management</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="868" data-end="880">BUSINESS</h3>
<ul data-start="881" data-end="921">
<li data-start="881" data-end="899">
<p data-start="883" data-end="899">Sales &amp; Orders</p>
</li>
<li data-start="900" data-end="921">
<p data-start="902" data-end="921">Finance &amp; Costing</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="923" data-end="935">PLATFORM</h3>
<ul data-start="936" data-end="959">
<li data-start="936" data-end="959">
<p data-start="938" data-end="959">Multi-Plant Support</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="961" data-end="975">That’s enough.</p>
<p data-start="977" data-end="993">Everything else:</p>
<ul data-start="994" data-end="1085">
<li data-start="994" data-end="1014">
<p data-start="996" data-end="1014">Smart Scheduling</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1015" data-end="1038">
<p data-start="1017" data-end="1038">Dispatch Automation</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1039" data-end="1055">
<p data-start="1041" data-end="1055">Traceability</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1056" data-end="1069">
<p data-start="1058" data-end="1069">Reporting</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1070" data-end="1085">
<p data-start="1072" data-end="1085">Role Access</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1087" data-end="1128">→ These should be explained inside pages.</p>
<hr data-start="1130" data-end="1133">
<h1 data-start="1135" data-end="1172">💡 Why Too Many Options Is Not Good</h1>
<p data-start="1174" data-end="1188">When you show:</p>
<p data-start="1190" data-end="1368">Production Planning<br data-start="1209" data-end="1212">
Smart Scheduling<br data-start="1228" data-end="1231">
Quality<br data-start="1238" data-end="1241">
Maintenance<br data-start="1252" data-end="1255">
Material Traceability<br data-start="1276" data-end="1279">
Dispatch<br data-start="1287" data-end="1290">
Live Stock<br data-start="1300" data-end="1303">
Procurement<br data-start="1314" data-end="1317">
Analytics<br data-start="1326" data-end="1329">
Role Based Access<br data-start="1346" data-end="1349">
Cloud<br data-start="1354" data-end="1357">
Workflows</p>
<p data-start="1370" data-end="1393">It starts looking like:</p>
<p data-start="1395" data-end="1466">⚠ Early-stage ERP<br data-start="1412" data-end="1415">
⚠ Feature list<br data-start="1429" data-end="1432">
⚠ Not strategic<br data-start="1447" data-end="1450">
⚠ Overwhelming</p>
<p data-start="1468" data-end="1521">Big SaaS companies never list everything in dropdown.</p>
<hr data-start="1523" data-end="1526">
<h1 data-start="1528" data-end="1562">🏆 My Honest Advice for Digizura</h1>
<p data-start="1564" data-end="1589">Keep mega menu strategic.</p>
<p data-start="1591" data-end="1602">Think like:</p>
<p data-start="1604" data-end="1646">"How do I position this as a serious ERP?"</p>
<p data-start="1648" data-end="1652">Not:</p>
<p data-start="1654" data-end="1684">"How do I list every feature?"</p>
<hr data-start="1686" data-end="1689">
<h1 data-start="1691" data-end="1738">🚀 Final Recommended Version (Strong &amp; Clean)</h1>
<p data-start="1740" data-end="1745">Keep:</p>
<p data-start="1747" data-end="1860">OPERATIONS → Production &amp; Quality<br data-start="1780" data-end="1783">
INVENTORY → Warehouse<br data-start="1804" data-end="1807">
BUSINESS → Sales &amp; Finance<br data-start="1833" data-end="1836">
PLATFORM → Multi-Plant</p>
<p data-start="1862" data-end="1870">And big:</p>
<p data-start="1872" data-end="1907"><strong data-start="1872" data-end="1907">Explore the CableMaker Platform</strong></p>
<p data-start="1909" data-end="1930">That feels confident.</p>
