b-a129b735b3a4" dir="auto" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-2" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="180">Yes — I see what you mean by the <strong data-start="33" data-end="48">Odoo design</strong> (based on the screenshot you shared):<br data-start="86" data-end="89">
It’s <strong data-start="94" data-end="148">much more dynamic, colorful, and visually engaging</strong> than your current Angular page.</p>
<p data-start="182" data-end="267">Here’s a breakdown of what makes the Odoo-style design attractive so we can model it:</p>
<hr data-start="269" data-end="272">
<h2 data-start="274" data-end="312">✅ Key Design Traits on Odoo Website</h2>
<h3 data-start="314" data-end="354">🟣 1. <strong data-start="324" data-end="354">Large, expressive headline</strong></h3>
<p data-start="355" data-end="365">Example:</p>
<blockquote data-start="366" data-end="440">
<p data-start="368" data-end="440"><em data-start="368" data-end="406">“All your business on one platform.”</em><br data-start="406" data-end="409">
with handwritten-style emphasis</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="442" data-end="516">Your page should have a similarly <em data-start="476" data-end="515">strong, emotionally engaging headline</em>.</p>
<hr data-start="518" data-end="521">
<h3 data-start="523" data-end="575">🎨 2. <strong data-start="533" data-end="575">Hand-drawn highlight and color accents</strong></h3>
<p data-start="576" data-end="586">Odoo uses:</p>
<ul data-start="587" data-end="661">
<li data-start="587" data-end="612">
<p data-start="589" data-end="612">Brush stroke highlights</p>
</li>
<li data-start="613" data-end="642">
<p data-start="615" data-end="642">Color emphasis on key words</p>
</li>
<li data-start="643" data-end="661">
<p data-start="645" data-end="661">Split typography</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="663" data-end="746">We <em data-start="666" data-end="681">already added</em> handwritten highlight — but Odoo’s use is larger and more fluid.</p>
<hr data-start="748" data-end="751">
<h3 data-start="753" data-end="803">🖼 3. <strong data-start="763" data-end="803">Illustrations and visuals everywhere</strong></h3>
<p data-start="804" data-end="834">Not just a static image — but:</p>
<ul data-start="836" data-end="898">
<li data-start="836" data-end="853">
<p data-start="838" data-end="853">Illustrations</p>
</li>
<li data-start="854" data-end="870">
<p data-start="856" data-end="870">Visual cards</p>
</li>
<li data-start="871" data-end="880">
<p data-start="873" data-end="880">Icons</p>
</li>
<li data-start="881" data-end="898">
<p data-start="883" data-end="898">Dynamic spacing</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="900" data-end="903">
<h3 data-start="905" data-end="951">📊 4. <strong data-start="915" data-end="951">Modular grid with clear sections</strong></h3>
<p data-start="952" data-end="961">They use:</p>
<ul data-start="963" data-end="1058">
<li data-start="963" data-end="979">
<p data-start="965" data-end="979">A hero section</p>
</li>
<li data-start="980" data-end="1007">
<p data-start="982" data-end="1007">Feature blocks with icons</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1008" data-end="1039">
<p data-start="1010" data-end="1039">Screenshots and illustrations</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1040" data-end="1058">
<p data-start="1042" data-end="1058">Animated reveals</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1060" data-end="1063">
<h3 data-start="1065" data-end="1105">🌀 5. <strong data-start="1075" data-end="1105">Curved background sections</strong></h3>
<p data-start="1106" data-end="1247">Odoo has soft waves and curve transitions between sections.<br data-start="1165" data-end="1168">
Your page is currently just plain color blocks — not enough visual personality.</p>
<hr data-start="1249" data-end="1252">
<h2 data-start="1254" data-end="1304">🔁 How to <em data-start="1267" data-end="1283">Translate That</em> to Your Angular Page</h2>
<p data-start="1306" data-end="1373">We need to upgrade your <code data-start="1330" data-end="1361">production-planning.component</code> to include:</p>
<ol data-start="1375" data-end="1602">
<li data-start="1375" data-end="1426">
<p data-start="1378" data-end="1426"><strong data-start="1378" data-end="1426">Dynamic Hero — with a big expressive message</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1427" data-end="1462">
<p data-start="1430" data-end="1462"><strong data-start="1430" data-end="1462">Decorative background shapes</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1463" data-end="1499">
<p data-start="1466" data-end="1499"><strong data-start="1466" data-end="1499">Icon + card grid for features</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1500" data-end="1537">
<p data-start="1503" data-end="1537"><strong data-start="1503" data-end="1537">Illustrations (SVG/PNG) inline</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1538" data-end="1577">
<p data-start="1541" data-end="1577"><strong data-start="1541" data-end="1577">Wave separators between sections</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1578" data-end="1602">
<p data-start="1581" data-end="1602"><strong data-start="1581" data-end="1602">Scroll animations</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="1604" data-end="1661">Here’s a blueprint that more closely matches Odoo’s feel.</p>
<hr data-start="1663" data-end="1666">
<h1 data-start="1668" data-end="1735">✅ Full Revised Angular Page (Production Planning — Odoo-Inspired)</h1>
<hr data-start="1737" data-end="1740">
<h2 data-start="1742" data-end="1784">⭕ 1. production-planning.component.html</h2>
