<p data-start="30" data-end="73">It’s <strong data-start="35" data-end="44">clean</strong>, but it’s still not premium.</p>
<p data-start="75" data-end="94">Right now it feels:</p>
<p data-start="96" data-end="277">• Too flat<br data-start="106" data-end="109">
• Too centered<br data-start="123" data-end="126">
• Too much empty white space<br data-start="154" data-end="157">
• Icons look like placeholders<br data-start="187" data-end="190">
• No depth / no visual hierarchy<br data-start="222" data-end="225">
• Looks like a student project, not a SaaS product</p>
<p data-start="279" data-end="317">That’s why you’re not fully satisfied.</p>
<hr data-start="319" data-end="322">
<h1 data-start="324" data-end="344">🎯 What’s Missing?</h1>
<p data-start="346" data-end="388">To look like Odoo-level quality, you need:</p>
<p data-start="390" data-end="592">✅ Background contrast (not plain white)<br data-start="429" data-end="432">
✅ Depth (shadows + layering)<br data-start="460" data-end="463">
✅ Better spacing rhythm<br data-start="486" data-end="489">
✅ Real icons (not just colored circles)<br data-start="528" data-end="531">
✅ Slight motion or hover interaction<br data-start="567" data-end="570">
✅ Section separation</p>
<hr data-start="594" data-end="597">
<h1 data-start="599" data-end="639">🔥 Let’s Upgrade That Section Properly</h1>
<p data-start="641" data-end="679">Instead of plain white, let’s make it:</p>
<p data-start="681" data-end="788">• Soft gradient background<br data-start="707" data-end="710">
• Elevated cards<br data-start="726" data-end="729">
• Bigger heading<br data-start="745" data-end="748">
• Better spacing<br data-start="764" data-end="767">
• More premium look</p>
