<p data-start="20" data-end="46">It’s clean… but it’s flat.</p>
<p data-start="48" data-end="66">What’s missing is:</p>
<p data-start="68" data-end="163">• Depth<br data-start="75" data-end="78">
• Contrast<br data-start="88" data-end="91">
• Visual tension<br data-start="107" data-end="110">
• Something breaking the grid<br data-start="139" data-end="142">
• Something premium</p>
<p data-start="165" data-end="240">Right now it looks like a documentation page.<br data-start="210" data-end="213">
Not a product company page.</p>
<p data-start="242" data-end="316">Let’s upgrade it properly — without ruining the clean structure you liked.</p>
<hr data-start="318" data-end="321">
<h1 data-start="323" data-end="361">🔥 Make It Premium (Without Clutter)</h1>
<p data-start="363" data-end="385">We’ll keep the layout.</p>
<p data-start="387" data-end="398">But we add:</p>
<ol data-start="400" data-end="610">
<li data-start="400" data-end="447">
<p data-start="403" data-end="447">Subtle background gradient (not plain white)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="448" data-end="508">
<p data-start="451" data-end="508">Big faint number behind heading (like premium SaaS sites)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="509" data-end="545">
<p data-start="512" data-end="545">Elevated visual mockup with depth</p>
</li>
<li data-start="546" data-end="574">
<p data-start="549" data-end="574">Slight offset positioning</p>
</li>
<li data-start="575" data-end="610">
<p data-start="578" data-end="610">Section divider for visual break</p>
</li>
</ol>
